data.title: 28 U.S. Code Part I - ORGANIZATION OF COURTS
authors: Office of the Law Revision Counsel
data.text:
Amendments

2002—Pub. L. 107–273, div. C, title I, § 11042(b), , 116 Stat. 1855, added item for chapter 16.

1992—Pub. L. 102–572, title IX, § 902(b)(1), , 106 Stat. 4516, substituted “United States Court of Federal Claims” for “United States Claims Court” in item for chapter 7.

1990—Pub. L. 101–650, title I, § 103(d), , 104 Stat. 5096, added item for chapter 23.

1984—Pub. L. 98–353, title I, § 104(b), , 98 Stat. 342, added item for chapter 6.

1982—Pub. L. 97–164, title I, §§ 105(b), 106, , 96 Stat. 28, substituted “United States Claims Court” for “Court of Claims” in item for chapter 7 and struck out item for chapter 9 “Court of Customs and Patent Appeals”.

1980—Pub. L. 96–417, title V, § 501(1), , 94 Stat. 1742, substituted “Court of International Trade” for “Customs Court” in item for chapter 11.
